<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="538" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="9.[130,778,1300,2028]" pageId="9" pageNumber="538">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kiefer" authorityYear="1938" box="[132,380,1331,1357]" class="Hexanauplia" family="Cyclopidae" genus="Acanthocyclops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="9" pageNumber="538" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="agamus">
<emphasis box="[132,380,1331,1357]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="538">Acanthocyclops agamus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described by 
<bibRefCitation author="KIEFER F." pageId="9" pageNumber="538" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref15808" refString="KIEFER F. 1938. - Cyclopiden (Crust. Cop.) aus suditalienischen Brunnen und Hohlen. Zoologischer Anzeiger 123 (1 / 2): 1 - 12." type="journal article" year="1938">Kiefer (1938)</bibRefCitation>
from a single male specimen from Castelcivita Cave. The original description raised doubts about the generic assignment of the species (
<bibRefCitation author="KIEFER F." box="[405,542,1427,1453]" pageId="9" pageNumber="538" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref15808" refString="KIEFER F. 1938. - Cyclopiden (Crust. Cop.) aus suditalienischen Brunnen und Hohlen. Zoologischer Anzeiger 123 (1 / 2): 1 - 12." type="journal article" year="1938">Kiefer 1938</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="DUSSART B." box="[555,707,1427,1454]" pageId="9" pageNumber="538" refId="ref14718" refString="DUSSART B. 1969. - Les Copepodes des eaux continentales d'Europe occidentale. II. CyclopoIdes et biologie. Boubee, Paris, 292 p." type="book" year="1969">Dussart 1969</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="DUSSART B. &amp; DEFAYE D." pageId="9" pageNumber="538" refId="ref14745" refString="DUSSART B. &amp; DEFAYE D. 1985. - Repertoire mondial des Copepodes CyclopoIdes. Editions du CNRS, Paris, 236 p." type="book" year="1985">Dussart &amp; Defaye 1985</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="EINSLE U." box="[362,494,1459,1486]" pageId="9" pageNumber="538" refId="ref14892" refString="EINSLE U. 1996. - Copepoda: Cyclopoida. Genera Cyclops, Megacyclops, Acanthocyclops, in DUMONT H. J. (Coordinating Editor), Guides to the Identification of the Microinvertebrates of the Continental Waters of the World, Vol. 10, SPB Academic Publishing, Amsterdam, 83 p." type="book" year="1996">Einsle 1996</bibRefCitation>
). Subsequently, 
<bibRefCitation author="GALASSI D. M. P. &amp; DE LAURENTIIS P." pageId="9" pageNumber="538" pagination="203 - 222" refId="ref15142" refString="GALASSI D. M. P. &amp; DE LAURENTIIS P. 2004 a. - Little-known cyclopoids from groundwater in Italy: re-validation of Acanthocyclops agamus and redescription of Speocyclops italicus (Crustacea, Copepoda, Cyclopoida). Vie et Milieu 54 (4): 203 - 222." type="journal article" year="2004">Galassi &amp; De Laurentiis (2004a)</bibRefCitation>
redescribed the species from topotypic males and females, confirming the validity of the species. At present, this stygobiotic species is known from the 
<typeStatus box="[691,737,1555,1581]" pageId="9" pageNumber="538">type</typeStatus>
locality in southern 
<collectingCountry box="[331,380,1586,1612]" name="Italy" pageId="9" pageNumber="538">Italy</collectingCountry>
, from the Mazzoccolo karstic spring (
<collectingRegion box="[140,221,1618,1644]" country="Italy" name="Lazio" pageId="9" pageNumber="538">Latium</collectingRegion>
, central 
<collectingCountry box="[305,353,1618,1645]" name="Italy" pageId="9" pageNumber="538">Italy</collectingCountry>
) and from the Gizio karstic spring (Abruzzi Region, central 
<collectingCountry box="[343,393,1650,1677]" name="Italy" pageId="9" pageNumber="538">Italy</collectingCountry>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="GALASSI D. M. P. &amp; DE LAURENTIIS P." box="[416,763,1650,1677]" pageId="9" pageNumber="538" pagination="203 - 222" refId="ref15142" refString="GALASSI D. M. P. &amp; DE LAURENTIIS P. 2004 a. - Little-known cyclopoids from groundwater in Italy: re-validation of Acanthocyclops agamus and redescription of Speocyclops italicus (Crustacea, Copepoda, Cyclopoida). Vie et Milieu 54 (4): 203 - 222." type="journal article" year="2004">Galassi &amp; De Laurentiis 2004a</bibRefCitation>
). The species shows unique features in the reduced segmental pattern of the swimming legs as result of heterochrony. The female shows an earlier arrested development than the male and consequently shows a more drastic and stable reduction in segmentation. This species is here recorded for the first time from areas outside the central-southern Apennines (
<collectingCountry box="[707,761,1841,1868]" name="Italy" pageId="9" pageNumber="538">Italy</collectingCountry>
), significantly expanding the distributional range of the species. At present, the species should be considered rare in both terms of abundance and patchiness in its geographic distribution, and for this reason it can be considered critically endangered according to the criteria of the 
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" box="[466,622,2001,2027]" pageId="9" pageNumber="538" refId="ref15586" refString="IUCN 2001. - IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 3.1. IUCN Species Survival Commission. IUCN, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK." type="book" year="2001">IUCN (2001)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
